{{Infobox Military Conflict |conflict=Battle of Feyiase |date=1701 |place=[[Feyiase]], [[Ghana]], [[West Africa]] |result=Decisive Asante victory; Fall of Denkyira kingdom and establishment of Asante Union |combatant1=[[Ashanti Empire]] |combatant2=Kingdom of [[Denkyira]] |commander1=Asantehene [[Osei Tutu]] |commander2=Denkyirahene [[Ntim Gyakari]]}}
The '''Battle of Feyiase''' was the decisive battle in the struggle that led to the [[Ashanti Empire]] replacing [[Denkyira]] as the dominant power among the [[Twi]]-speaking [[Akan people|Akan]] peoples.
Prior to this battle the Denkyirahene [[Ntim Gyakari]] thought he was doing well in the war, having driven the [[Ashanti Empire|Ashanti]] (Asante) forces from Adunku, Abuontem and Aputuogya. However this was all part of [[Osei Tutu]]'s plan to ambush the Denkyira troops at Feyiase.
At Feyiase the full force of the Asante war machine fell upon the Denkyiran army, and they were routed. [[Ntim Gyakari]] was killed by the people of Adunku from Asante Feyiase, and Denkyira's [[hegemony]] was broken at Feyiase Akoyem. Feyiase Akoyem is now a part of [[Bosomtwe District]] which lies between Aputuogya and Esereso where the war ended<ref>https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/regional/Feyiase-Akoyem-gets-new-police-station-290171</ref>.
== References == {{refbegin}} *McCaskie, T. C. "Denkyira in the Making of Asante" in ''The Journal of African History''. vol. 48 (2007), no. 1, p. 3. {{refend}}
