The '''Brondings''' were a [[Germanic peoples|Germanic tribe]]. They and [[Breca the Bronding]] are mentioned in ''[[Beowulf]]'' (Th. 1047; B. 521.), as [[Beowulf (hero)|Beowulf]]'s childhood friend, and in ''[[Widsith]]'' (Scóp Th. 51; Wíd. 25.), where Breca is the lord of the Brondings. They were probably the people of the Swedish island of [[Brännö]], west of [[Gothenburg]] in the [[Kattegatt]].

