The [[Bushongo (people)|Bushongo]] or [[Songora]] are an ethnic group from the [[Congo River]] and surrounding areas. The creation god(or chembe) in '''Bushongo mythology''' is called [[Bumba (god)|Bumba]]. He existed alone in darkness, the world consisting only of water.  The god Bumba was said to appear like a gigantic man in form and white in color.<ref>{{cite web|last=Torday|first=E.|title=Bushongo Mythology|url=https://www.jstor.org/discover/10.2307/1254954?uid=3739840&uid=2129&uid=2&uid=70&uid=4&uid=3739256&sid=21101301969251|work=Folklore, Vol. 22 N1, pp.v 41-47|publisher=Folklore Enterprises Ltd.|accessdate=24 October 2012}}</ref>   The [[creation myth|creation]] took place when he vomited forth the [[sun]], [[moon]], [[earth]], [[plant]]s and [[animal]]s, and then [[human]]ity. [[Bomazi]] is the ancestor-god of the Bushongo.

