'''João da Mata Chapuzet''' (1777 – 8 August 1842) was a Portuguese colonial administrator and a military architect.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=43oNAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA416&dq=Chapuzet,+Jo%C3%A3o+da+Mata&hl=pt-PT&sa=X&ei=SVYxT9zsB8LP0QWg0ZGiBw&ved=0CEsQ6AEwBA#v=onepage&q=Chapuzet%2C%20Jo%C3%A3o%20da%20Mata&f=false|title= Diccionário bibliográphico portuguez: estudos|publisher=Imprensa Nacional|date=7 February 2012}}</ref> He was [[List of colonial governors of Cape Verde|colonial governor of Cape Verde]], succeeding [[António Pusich]] on 16 January 1823. He was succeeded as governor by [[Caetano Procópio Godinho de Vasconcelos]] on 13 December 1826.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldstatesmen.org/Cape_Verde.html|title=Cape Verde|website=worldstatesmen.org}}</ref> Governor Chapuzet initiated the modernisation of the city of Praia.<ref name=gomes>[http://hdl.handle.net/11328/594 Valor simbólico do centro histórico da Praia], Lourenço Conceição Gomes, Universidade Portucalense, 2008, p. 315</ref> 

