[[File:LCGBLogo.jpg|thumb|LCGB Logo]] The '''Luxembourg Confederation of Christian Trade Unions''' ({{lang-lb|Lëtzebuerger Chrëschtleche Gewerkschaftsbond}}, {{lang-fr|Confédération Luxembourgeoise des Syndicats Chrétiens}}), abbreviated to '''LCGB''', is a [[Luxembourg]]ish [[trade union]] confederation. As the LCGB abides by the principles of Christian social teachings. This is also illustrated by the trade union's motto: Man at the Center of our action.
By membership, the LCGB is the second-largest trade union federation in the country, with a little over 40,000 members.
The LCGB has its headquarters not far from the central trainway station in Luxembourg-City.
==Organization of LCGB==
===On the national and local scale=== {{Emptysection|date=February 2013}}
===LCGB's offices=== {{Emptysection|date=February 2013}}
===On the international, european and regional scale=== On the international scale, the LCGB is affiliated to the [[International Trade Union Confederation]] (ITUC) and the [[European Trade Union Confederation]] (ETUC).
On the regional scale ("Grande Région"), the LCGB is a member of the IGR Saar-Lor-Lux/Trier-Westpfalz, the IRS 3 Frontières and the Plateforme syndicale de la Grande Région (PSGR). As such, two EURES-councillors are working at LCGB.
