'''The Killers of Comedy Tour''' features cast and regulars from ''[[The Howard Stern Show]]'' such as [[Reverend Bob Levy]], [[Sal Governale]], [[Richard Christy]], [[Jim Florentine]], [[Yucko the Clown]] and [[Shuli]] performing [[stand up comedy]]. On occasion, [[Beetlejuice (entertainer)|Beetlejuice]], [[Gary the Conqueror]], [[The Wack Pack#Bigfoot (Mark Shaw, Jr.)|Bigfoot]] and [[The Iron Sheik]] participate. A recurring joke is Bob Levy eating [[blue cheese]] or [[whipped cream]] out of a woman's rear end. It also featured up and coming stand up comedians like John Tole & Brad Thacker who toured & hosted the shows.
Howard Stern's sidekick, [[Artie Lange]], referred to the group as the "Hack Pack" in July, 2007. The name, which has since been unofficially adopted by the troup, caused controversy when Shuli confronted Artie on air and told him how offended he was.<ref>{{cite web|first=Jason|last=Kaplan|author2=Michael Dempster |title=The Rundown - The "Hack Pack" Attacks a Fat Man|date=2007-07-25|publisher=HowardStern.com|url=http://howardstern.com/rundown.hs?month=July&day=25&year=2007 |accessdate=2007-09-04|quote=Shuli came in to complain about Artie calling the Killers of Comedy "The Hack Pack" on the RawDog comedy channel.}}</ref> Earlier in the show, Artie had remarked about John, Ralph, and himself becoming the new "[[Rat Pack]]" in [[Las Vegas, Nevada|Vegas]], noting that "Sad Pack" was a more apt description.<ref>{{cite web|first=Jason|last=Kaplan|author2=Michael Dempster |title=The Rundown - The Sad Pack Rides Again|date=2007-07-25 |publisher=HowardStern.com |url=http://howardstern.com/rundown.hs?month=July&day=25&year=2007|accessdate=2007-09-05|quote=...noting that the three of them in Vegas would be the new "Rat Pack," although he thought "Sad Pack" was a better title.}}</ref>
